        <descriptionSet>
            <description>Issue number 14 of John Marr's "Murder Can Be Fun" zine tells the story of "going postal," looking at the history of shootings in post offices and how the postal workers were usually the victims of the crime, rather than the perpetrators. The issue also examines the history of riots in the U.S. and looks at other odd stories, including the great Nashville Train Wreck of 1918.</description>
